query.queryCore: DECLARE @StartInterval  date = ? DECLARE @EndInterval date = ?      DECLARE @tbl TABLE (iterday DATE);  ;WITH seq(n) AS  (   SELECT 0 UNION ALL SELECT n + 1 FROM seq   WHERE n < DATEDIFF(DAY, @StartInterval, @EndInterval) ), d(d) AS  (   SELECT DATEADD(DAY, n, @StartInterval) FROM seq ) INSERT INTO @tbl SELECT d OneDay  FROM d ORDER BY d OPTION (MAXRECURSION 0);  WITH r as 	( SELECT  [Reservation].[id] 		,[Reservation].[bedId] 		,CAST(reservationStart -0.5  AS date) startMinus12H 		,CAST(reservationEnd - 0.5  AS date) endMinus12H 	FROM [HMSOps].[lodging].[Reservation] 	WHERE [Reservation].[timeRetired] IS NULL  		AND [Reservation].[timeCreated] < GETDATE()  		AND [Reservation].[reservationStart] < @EndInterval ) SELECT 	r.[id] 		,r.[bedId] 		,YEAR(t.iterday) * 10000 + MONTH(t.iterday) * 100 + DAY(t.iterday) iterday 	FROM r	   		INNER JOIN @tbl t ON iterday>= startMinus12H AND iterday <= endMinus12H 		INNER JOIN [HMSOps].[lodging].[Bed] ON r.[bedId] = [Bed].[id] 		INNER JOIN [HMSOps].[lodging].[Room] ON [Bed].[roomId] = [Room].[id] 		INNER JOIN [HMSOps].[lodging].[Facility] ON [Room].[facilityId] = [Facility].[id] 	WHERE (1=1)

customMethods.name: setByWherePlusIn
customMethods.script:
import extend.query
	
	tbl = self.getChild("Table")
	
	if not(wherePlusIn):
		tbl.props.data = []
	
	## Because this is special case (special table), only wherePlusIn props is taken from props
	#wherePlusIn_0 = self.view.params.wherePlusIn
	
	#system.perspective.print(('old self.view.params.wherePlusIn:', self.view.params.wherePlusIn))
	
	wherePlusIn_0 = wherePlusIn

	
	###Facility - Room -Bed #########################################################################################
	try:
		facilityObj = {'arg':wherePlusIn_0[2]['arg']}
		if wherePlusIn_0[2].get('type'):
			facilityObj['type'] = wherePlusIn_0[2].get('type')
		facilityObj['cnd'] = "-1 = ?" if facilityObj['arg'] == -1 else "[Facility].[id] in (?)"
		wherePlusBed = [facilityObj]
	except:
		wherePlusBed = None
				
	if not(wherePlusBed):
		tbl.props.data = []
		return	
		
	queryCoreBed = """SELECT [Facility].[id] AS facilityId, [Room].[id] AS roomId, [Bed].[id] AS bedId, 
			[Facility].[facilityName], [Room].[roomName], [Bed].[bedName]
	FROM [lodging].[Bed]
		INNER JOIN [lodging].[Room] ON [Bed].[roomId] = [Room].[id]
		INNER JOIN [lodging].[Facility] ON [Room].[facilityId] = [Facility].[id]
	WHERE ([Facility].[timeRetired] is NULL 
		AND [Room].[timeRetired] is NULL
		AND [Bed].[timeRetired] is NULL) """

	orderbyBed = """[Facility].[facilityName], [Room].[roomName], [Bed].[bedName]"""

	queryBed, argsBed = extend.query.getPrepQueryArgs(queryCoreBed, wherePlusBed, orderbyBed)
	
	resultBed = system.db.runPrepQuery(queryBed,argsBed,'HMSOps') 
	
	if resultBed.rowCount == 0:
		tbl.props.data = []
		return			
	
	lstBedFr = [[x['bedId'],x['facilityName'],x['roomName'],x['bedName']] for x in system.dataset.toPyDataSet(resultBed)]
	
	argsBedId = [x['bedId'] for x in system.dataset.toPyDataSet(resultBed)]
	
	###Bed - Reserved Days#########################################################################################
	# Query to get reservations. If interval reservationStart or reservationEnd is out of @StartInterval and @EndInterval
	# these dates are changed with @StartInterval and @EndInterval.
	queryReservedBedCore = """
	DECLARE @StartInterval date = ?   
	DECLARE @EndInterval date = ? 
	
	SELECT [Reservation].[id] ,[Reservation].[bedId] ,    
	CASE WHEN reservationStart < @StartInterval THEN @StartInterval 
			ELSE CAST(reservationStart AS date) END AS reservationStart ,   
	CASE WHEN ISNULL([Reservation].[reservationEnd],@EndInterval) > @EndInterval THEN @EndInterval 
			ELSE CAST(ISNULL([Reservation].[reservationEnd],@EndInterval) AS date) END AS reservationEnd   
	FROM [lodging].[Reservation]  
	WHERE ([Reservation].[timeRetired] IS NULL
	AND [Reservation].[reservationStart] IS NOT NULL    
	AND CAST([Reservation].[reservationStart] AS date) <= @EndInterval
	AND CAST(ISNULL([Reservation].[reservationEnd],@EndInterval) AS date) >= @StartInterval)
	"""
	# Note: use list of bedIds  (argsBedId) as arg value in 3rd item
	wherePlusIn = [	{'arg': wherePlusIn_0[0]['arg'], type: 'datetime', 'cnd': None}
	,{'arg': wherePlusIn_0[1]['arg'], type: 'datetime', 'cnd': None}
	,{'arg': argsBedId, 'cnd': '[Reservation].[bedId] in (?)'}
	]
	
	queryReservedBed, args = extend.query.getPrepQueryArgs(queryReservedBedCore, wherePlus=wherePlusIn, orderby=None, useCnd = True)

	resultReservedBed = system.db.runPrepQuery(queryReservedBed, args, 'HMSOps') 	
	
	# For example lstReservedBed = [...]
	# This is list of lists where one item contains reservation: id, bedid, dayStart, dayEnd
	lstReservedBed =[list(x) for x in system.dataset.toPyDataSet(resultReservedBed)]


	###Bed - Occupied Days#########################################################################################
	# Query to get occupation. If interval eventStart or eventEnd is out of @StartInterval and @EndInterval
	# these dates are changed with @StartInterval and @EndInterval.
	queryOccupiedBedCore = """
	DECLARE @StartInterval date = ?   
	DECLARE @EndInterval date = ? 
	
	SELECT [BedLog].[id] ,[BedLog].[bedId] ,    
	CASE WHEN eventStart < @StartInterval THEN @StartInterval 
			ELSE CAST(eventStart AS date) END AS eventStart ,   
	CASE WHEN ISNULL([BedLog].[eventEnd],@EndInterval) > @EndInterval THEN @EndInterval 
			ELSE CAST(ISNULL([BedLog].[eventEnd],@EndInterval) AS date) END AS eventEnd   
	FROM [lodging].[BedLog]  
	WHERE ([BedLog].[eventStart] IS NOT NULL    
	AND CAST([BedLog].[eventStart] AS date) <= @EndInterval
	AND CAST(ISNULL([BedLog].[eventEnd],@EndInterval) AS date) >= @StartInterval)
	"""
	
	# Change cnd in 3rd node
	wherePlusIn[2]['cnd'] = "[BedLog].[bedId] in (?)"
	
	queryOccupiedBed, args = extend.query.getPrepQueryArgs(queryOccupiedBedCore, wherePlus=wherePlusIn, orderby=None, useCnd = True)
		
	resultOccupiedBed = system.db.runPrepQuery(queryOccupiedBed, args, 'HMSOps') 
	
	# This is list of lists where one item contains occupation: id, bedid, dayStart, dayEnd	
	lstOccupiedBed =[list(x) for x in system.dataset.toPyDataSet(resultOccupiedBed)]	


	###Start and End Date #########################################################################################
	#t1, t2 = args[0], args[1]
	t1 = system.date.parse(wherePlusIn[0]['arg']) 
	t2 = system.date.parse(wherePlusIn[1]['arg'])
	#ystem.perspective.print(('t12', t1, t2, type(t1), tm1, tm2, type(tm1)))
	lstDates = self.getDaysBetween(t1, t2)
	#lst4Y2M2D = [system.date.getYear(t)*10000 + (system.date.getMonth(t) + 1)*100 + system.date.getDayOfMonth(t) for t in lstDates]
	lst4Y2M2D = [int(system.date.format(x,'yyyyMMdd')) for x in lstDates]
	
	###Check if current day todayClient is inside requested interval, and find index inside lst4Y2M2D
	timeClientOffset = self.session.props.device.timezone.utcOffset - system.date.getTimezoneOffset()
	todayClient = system.date.addMinutes(system.date.now(),int(timeClientOffset*60))
	todayClient4Y2M2D = int(system.date.format(todayClient,'yyyyMMdd'))
	todayIndex = lst4Y2M2D.index(todayClient4Y2M2D) if todayClient4Y2M2D in lst4Y2M2D else None
	todayIndex = todayIndex + 5 if todayIndex is not None else None
	
	###Header grouping year month##################################################################################
	lstHeaderGroups = self.getHeaderGroups(lstDates)
	tbl.props.enableHeaderGroups = True
	tbl.props.headerGroups = lstHeaderGroups

	
	###Fix props columns##################################################################################
	fields = ['Options','bedId','facilityName','roomName','bedName'] + ['x'+str(x) for x in lst4Y2M2D]
	widths = [50,50,180,140,100]+len(lst4Y2M2D)*[25] 
	justify = ['left','left','left','left','left'] + len(lst4Y2M2D)*['center']
	#headerTitles = ['bedId','Facility','Room','Bed']+[str(x)[-2:] for x in lst4Y2M2D]	
	headerTitles = [' ','bedId','Facility','Room','Bed']+[str(x)[-2:] for x in lst4Y2M2D]	
	
	tbl.props.columns = self.getColumnsProps(fields = fields, widths = widths, headerTitles = headerTitles,justify = justify, todayIndex = todayIndex)
	
	###Fix data and appereance##################################################################################
	
	#ystem.perspective.print(('b1', lstReservedBed,lstBedFr, lst4Y2M2D))

	matrix = self.getMatrix(lstReservedBed,lstOccupiedBed, lstBedFr, lst4Y2M2D)

	matrix = self.getMakeUp(matrix, fields, todayIndex)
	
	tbl.props.data = matrix

customMethods.name: getDaysBetween
customMethods.script:
dateList = []
	
	if system.date.isBefore(t1, t2):
		k = 1
	else:
		t1, t2 = t2, t1
		k = -1
	
	t = t1
	
	# use t2_day_after to include also t2
	t2_day_after = system.date.addDays(t2, 1)
	while system.date.isBefore(t, t2_day_after):
		dateList.append(t)
		t = system.date.addDays(t,1)
		if t == t2_day_after:
			break

	return dateList[::k]

customMethods.name: getColumnsProps
customMethods.script:
jsonAtom = """{
	  "visible": true,
	  "resizable": true,
	  "dateFormat": "MM/DD/YYYY",
	  "footer": {
	    "justify": "left",
	    "style": { "classes": "" },
	    "title": "",
	    "align": "center"
	  },
	  "editable": true,
	  "sortable": true,
	  "sort": "none",
	  "align": "center",
	  "viewPath": "",
	  "number": "value",
	  "boolean": "checkbox",
	  "strictWidth": false,
	  "field": "bedId",
	  "numberFormat": "0,0.##",
	  "justify": "auto",
	  "progressBar": {
	    "bar": { "color": "", "style": { "classes": "" } },
	    "min": 0,
	    "max": 100,
	    "track": { "color": "", "style": { "classes": "" } },
	    "value": {
	      "justify": "center",
	      "format": "0,0.##",
	      "style": { "classes": "" },
	      "enabled": true
	    }
	  },
	  "width": "",
	  "header": {
	    "justify": "left",
	    "style": { "classes": "" },
	    "title": "",
	    "align": "center"
	  },
	  "toggleSwitch": { "color": { "unselected": "", "selected": "" } },
	  "style": {},
	  "viewParams": {},
	  "render": "auto"
	}"""
	
	pyList = []
	lstCol = []
	for i in range(len(fields)):
		pyAtom = system.util.jsonDecode(jsonAtom)
		pyAtom['field'] = fields[i]
		pyAtom['sortable'] = False
		pyAtom['editable'] = False
		pyAtom['strictWidth'] = True
		pyAtom['width'] = widths[i]
		pyAtom['justify'] = justify[i]
		pyAtom['header']['title'] = headerTitles[i]
		pyAtom['header']['justify'] = justify[i]
		pyAtom['header']['style']= {'classes':'Table/Column_Header_Detail_Small'}
		
		if fields[i] == 'Options':
			pyAtom['render'] = 'view'
			pyAtom['viewPath'] = 'Shelter/Schedule/Components/TableOptions'
		
		if fields[i] == 'bedId':
			pyAtom["visible"] = False
		
		pyList.append(pyAtom)
	
	return pyList

customMethods.name: getHeaderGroups
customMethods.script:
lst_4Y_4Y2M = [[system.date.getYear(t),system.date.getYear(t)*100 + (system.date.getMonth(t) + 1)] for t in lstDates]
	#ystem.perspective.print((lst_4Y2M_monthName))
	
	lst4Y, lst4Y2M = [], [] 
	for x in lst_4Y_4Y2M:
		lst4Y.append(x[0])
		lst4Y2M.append(x[1])
	
	
	
	from itertools import groupby
	count4Y2M = [len(list(group)) for key, group in groupby(lst4Y2M)]
	unique4Y2M = sorted(list(set(lst4Y2M)))
	
	dictMonths = {}
	for i in range(12):
		dictMonths[i+1] = system.date.format(system.date.getDate(1973,i,1),'MMMM').upper()

	count4Y = [len(list(group)) for key, group in groupby(lst4Y)]
	unique4Y = sorted(list(set(lst4Y)))
	
	# If props is same for all grouped header, value could be set in jAtom
	jAtom = """{
	  "title": "",
	  "span": 2,
	  "justify": "center",
	  "align": "center",
	  "style": {
	    "classes": "Table/Column_Header_Detail_Small"
	  }
	}"""
	
	# "Table/Column_Header_Detail"
	
	lstHeaderGroup = []
	pyAtom = system.util.jsonDecode(jAtom)
	pyAtom['title'] = ''
	pyAtom['span'] = 4
	lstY = [pyAtom]
	
	pyAtom = system.util.jsonDecode(jAtom)
	pyAtom['title'] = ''
	pyAtom['span'] = 4
	lstYM = [pyAtom]
	for i in range(len(unique4Y2M)):
		pyAtom = system.util.jsonDecode(jAtom)
		monthInt = unique4Y2M[i] % 100 
		pyAtom['title'] = dictMonths[monthInt][:3] + ' ' +  unicode(int(unique4Y2M[i] / 100)) if count4Y2M[i] > 3 else dictMonths[monthInt][:3] 
		pyAtom['span'] = count4Y2M[i]
		#pyAtom['style']['classes'] = 'Table/Column_Header_Detail_Small' 
		lstYM.append(pyAtom)
	lstHeaderGroup.append(lstYM)		
	
	return lstHeaderGroup

customMethods.name: getMatrix
customMethods.script:
# Final list of list (matrix)
	pyList = []
	# First step: First 4 columns are bedId, facility name, room name, bed name (lstBedFr)  and others are day columns (lst4Y2M2D:
	# Fill table (matrix) with 0. 
	for bed in lstBedFr:
		pyList.append([bed[0],bed[1],bed[2],bed[3]]+len(lst4Y2M2D)*[0])
	
	lstBed = [x[0] for x in lstBedFr]
	
	# Example: lstReservedBed -> [[22, 101, 2020-08-13 00:00:00.0, 2020-08-14 00:00:00.0], [27, 42, 2020-08-13 00:00:00.0, 2020-08-27 00:00:00.0]]
	# dates are in format java.util.date

	# Fill cells according reservation. 1 mean bed is reserved for that day
	for item in lstReservedBed:
		r = lstBed.index(item[1]) # item[1] is bed id and it is unique number in lstBed (list of Bed ids) 
		auxDays = self.getDaysBetween(item[2], item[3]) # item[2], item[3] are dates reservationStart and reservationEnd inside requested interval
		days =  [int(system.date.format(x,'yyyyMMdd')) for x in auxDays]
		for day in days:
			c = lst4Y2M2D.index(day) # item[1] is day as yyyyMMdd and it is unique number in lst4Y2M2D (list of days in format yyyyMMdd) 
			pyList[r][c+4] = 1 
			
	# Fill cellsbed-occupation. 2 mean bed is occupied for that day
	for item in lstOccupiedBed:
		r = lstBed.index(item[1]) # item[1] is bed id and it is unique number in lstBed (list of Bed ids) 
		auxDays = self.getDaysBetween(item[2], item[3]) # item[2], item[3] are dates eventStart and eventEnd inside requested interval
		days =  [int(system.date.format(x,'yyyyMMdd')) for x in auxDays]
		for day in days:
			c = lst4Y2M2D.index(day) 
			pyList[r][c+4] = 2	
	
	
	#ystem.perspective.print(('pyList', pyList))	
	return pyList
